section:
  Coverages


These functions operate on sets of polygonal geometry that form "implicit coverages".
      To form a valid coverage polygons must not overlap, and the vertices of adjacent edges must match exactly.
      Coverages are fast to process, and can be operated on with window functions, which retain the coverage topology inside the window partition while altering the edges.





